<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1761,2037]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicName authority="(Bezzi, 1909)" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[151,594,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macerrimus">
<emphasis box="[151,436,1762,1785]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Macrostomus macerrimus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[452,586,1761,1786]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="293 - 407" refId="ref14174" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, 91, 293 - 407." type="journal article" year="1909">Bezzi, 1909</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is tentatively being treated in the 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1135,1761,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipennis">
<emphasis box="[970,1135,1761,1785]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">M. limbipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group as described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[189,498,1797,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="45 - 55" refId="ref14826" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2012) Revision of the genus Macrostomus Wiedemann (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). III. The limbipennis species-group. Zootaxa, 3361, 45 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0044 - 59672010000300023" type="journal article" year="2012">Rafael &amp; Cumming (2012)</bibRefCitation>
with the following characters: 1–2 pairs of ocellar setae, posterior pair weaker; 1 postsutural supra-alar seta; tergite 8 with deep posterior sinus; epandrium with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes approximately of same length; hypandrium with apex wider than base and ejaculatory apodeme tetralamellar. Additionally, two new species are also being included in this species-group, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Marques, 2019" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Marques" authorityYear="2019" box="[1076,1229,1906,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1076,1229,1906,1929]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">M. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1243,1339,1905,1930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1339,1905,1930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Marques, 2019" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Marques" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rodriguezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">M. rodriguezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,367,1941,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[276,361,1941,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, however, these two species differ by possessing tergite 8 somewhat short with shallow distal sinus; epandrium with posterodorsal lobe longer than anterodorsal lobe; hypandrium almost same width from base to apex.
</paragraph>
